WEBVTT

00:00.626 --> 00:02.544
♪ ♪

00:04.796 --> 00:06.173
Hey, girls, what's up

00:06.173 --> 00:08.717
Well, we decided
to talk in rhyme.

00:08.717 --> 00:10.719
So now we do it
all the time.

00:10.719 --> 00:13.555
As for rhymes, we have a ton.

00:13.555 --> 00:15.849
So please don't ask
when we'll be done.

00:16.433 --> 00:19.436
Oh, I think I could go
on a fun run in the sun.

00:20.187 --> 00:21.230
Hun.

00:22.314 --> 00:23.482
Okay, now it's done.

00:25.359 --> 00:27.194
Dad, I know that
Olive slept over

00:27.194 --> 00:29.613
the last two nights
already, but...

00:29.613 --> 00:31.198
can she stay another?

00:31.198 --> 00:33.951
We've been having
so much fun, Mr. R.

00:33.951 --> 00:35.827
I don't know, girls.
It's Sunday.

00:35.827 --> 00:37.412
Tomorrow's school.
That's a big ask.

00:37.412 --> 00:40.165
Please? I wouldn't ask it
unless I was asking

00:40.165 --> 00:43.168
the best dad in
the whole wide world.

00:43.168 --> 00:45.212
"In the whole
wide world," huh?

00:45.212 --> 00:46.672
Syd, I see what
you're doing.

00:46.672 --> 00:49.925
Of course you do.
You're the smartest dad
there is.

00:50.509 --> 00:51.510
Really?

00:53.303 --> 00:54.638
Okay, well, let me
call Olive's mom

00:54.638 --> 00:55.514
and see if she's okay with it.

00:56.139 --> 00:57.307
(quietly):
Yes!

01:01.353 --> 01:03.563
(tapping, ringing)

01:04.314 --> 01:06.817
<i>Max? Is Olive okay?!</i>

01:06.817 --> 01:09.236
<i>Is it her allergies?</i>
<i>Did her pinkeye come back?</i>

01:09.236 --> 01:11.154
<i>Um, I have eye drops.</i>
<i>If I take the alley,</i>

01:11.154 --> 01:12.656
<i>I can be there</i>
<i>in three minutes.</i>

01:13.574 --> 01:14.950
No, no. Olive is fine.

01:14.950 --> 01:17.119
I just called because the girls
wanna extend their sleepover

01:17.119 --> 01:19.037
another night.
What do you think?

01:19.705 --> 01:21.957
<i>Well, I mean, normally I'd be</i>
<i>against it on a school night,</i>

01:21.957 --> 01:25.127
<i>but I guess it's okay,</i>
<i>given the situation at home.</i>

01:25.544 --> 01:26.587
What situation?

01:28.380 --> 01:29.298
Well?

01:30.257 --> 01:31.800
Congratulations.
You got another night!

01:31.800 --> 01:33.302
(both squeal)

01:33.302 --> 01:35.262
Now we have time to do
makeovers on each other!

01:35.262 --> 01:36.930
And this time,
I promise not to sneeze

01:36.930 --> 01:38.098
and get lipstick
up your nose.

01:40.267 --> 01:41.893
Uh, Syd, can I talk
to you for a minute?

01:42.269 --> 01:44.604
Uh, of course.
Right behind you.

01:44.604 --> 01:45.647
What's up?

01:46.106 --> 01:48.108
Why didn't you tell me Olive's
parents are getting divorced?

01:48.775 --> 01:50.402
What?

01:50.986 --> 01:53.697
Olive's parents
are getting divorced?

01:53.697 --> 01:55.449
(theme music playing)

01:57.492 --> 01:59.953
<i>♪ Like father, like daughter,</i>
<i>we don't always agree ♪</i>

01:59.953 --> 02:02.706
<i>♪ But looking at you</i>
<i>is like looking at me ♪</i>

02:02.706 --> 02:07.377
<i>♪ The more things change,</i>
<i>the more they stay the same ♪</i>

02:07.377 --> 02:09.796
<i>♪ Like father, like daughter,</i>
<i>from different times ♪</i>

02:09.796 --> 02:11.923
<i>♪ Taking all the best</i>
<i>from your decade and mine ♪</i>

02:11.923 --> 02:15.844
<i>♪ The more things change ♪</i>

02:15.844 --> 02:17.304
<i>♪ The more they stay the same ♪</i>

02:17.304 --> 02:20.599
<i>♪ Do do, do do do do,</i>
<i>do do ♪</i>

02:20.599 --> 02:22.142
<i>♪ The more they stay the same ♪</i>

02:24.561 --> 02:26.188
♪ ♪

02:26.647 --> 02:29.775
I can't believe Olive's
parents are getting divorced.

02:30.442 --> 02:32.569
‐Are you sure?
‐Yeah, her mom just told me.

02:32.569 --> 02:33.862
So Olive didn't tell you?

02:33.862 --> 02:35.280
No. She didn't say anything.

02:36.490 --> 02:39.242
Oh my gosh. Poor Olive.

02:39.242 --> 02:41.119
She must be devastated.

02:41.119 --> 02:43.455
I bet.
When my parents got divorced,

02:43.455 --> 02:45.415
I felt like the world
was ending.

02:45.791 --> 02:47.709
Must've been awful.

02:47.709 --> 02:49.044
It's just so weird. I mean,

02:49.044 --> 02:51.046
Olive's been
here all weekend,

02:51.046 --> 02:52.839
and she's acting like
nothing's going on.

02:52.839 --> 02:54.675
Well, maybe that's why
she wanted to sleep over

02:54.675 --> 02:56.718
the last few nights.
She probably
doesn't wanna face it.

02:57.135 --> 02:59.805
Wow. I wonder why
she didn't tell me.

03:00.263 --> 03:02.182
Everybody handles these
things differently, Syd.

03:02.974 --> 03:04.476
I'm sure Olive
has her reasons.

03:05.060 --> 03:07.062
Yeah, but now I know.

03:07.062 --> 03:08.563
What do I do?

03:08.563 --> 03:10.232
Should I say something?
Should I not say something?

03:10.232 --> 03:12.275
Am I supposed to just
go back upstairs

03:12.275 --> 03:13.568
and pretend like
everything's normal?

03:14.152 --> 03:16.279
I know it's tough, but...

03:16.279 --> 03:17.906
Olive will tell you
when she's ready.

03:17.906 --> 03:19.866
You're probably right, Dad.

03:20.951 --> 03:22.828
It's not gonna be easy,
but I just gotta

03:22.828 --> 03:24.996
play it cool and wait
for her to open up.

03:30.252 --> 03:32.295
Hey! Sorry I took so long.

03:32.295 --> 03:33.797
No worries. All good.

03:33.797 --> 03:35.841
Okay! Makeover time.

03:35.841 --> 03:38.385
Uh, Syd, listen.

03:38.385 --> 03:39.970
Before we start, there's
something I should tell you.

03:40.971 --> 03:42.597
Oh, Olive!

03:42.597 --> 03:44.391
You can tell me anything!

03:44.391 --> 03:46.518
I'm here for you,
no matter what!

03:46.935 --> 03:49.146
I got blush on your bench.

03:50.564 --> 03:51.648
Say what?

03:54.151 --> 03:56.945
Oh. Gee, you sure did.

03:56.945 --> 03:58.405
Why all the emotion?

03:59.364 --> 04:01.032
I just hate to think that

04:01.032 --> 04:03.160
you've been carrying
this secret for

04:03.160 --> 04:04.494
who knows how long?

04:04.911 --> 04:07.706
It happened five minutes ago.

04:08.415 --> 04:11.793
Yeah, but those five minutes
must've been a nightmare.

04:13.670 --> 04:17.048
You found out my parents are
getting divorced, didn't you?

04:17.048 --> 04:18.758
Yeah.

04:18.758 --> 04:21.094
I'm so sorry, Olive.

04:21.094 --> 04:22.679
I can't imagine how
you're feeling right now.

04:23.096 --> 04:24.848
Actually, I'm fine.

04:26.767 --> 04:29.186
‐You are?
‐Yeah.

04:29.186 --> 04:30.312
They're the ones
getting divorced,

04:30.312 --> 04:31.313
not me.

04:31.855 --> 04:33.648
But it's still gonna
be hard on you.

04:33.648 --> 04:35.108
Not really.

04:35.108 --> 04:36.735
Now, can we just get
back to makeovers?

04:38.278 --> 04:40.030
Sure. Of course.

04:42.240 --> 04:45.076
You know, there is something
else I wanted to say.

04:45.410 --> 04:47.621
Yes! Let it out!

04:47.996 --> 04:50.499
I also got eyeshadow
on your rug.

04:52.083 --> 04:55.337
♪ ♪

04:55.337 --> 04:57.714
Okay, Max. While your
dad is watching you,

04:57.714 --> 04:59.466
I want you in bed by 9,

04:59.466 --> 05:02.636
eating healthy,
and showering every day.

05:02.636 --> 05:05.639
Mom, you're just
asking me to lie to you,

05:05.639 --> 05:07.557
but okay.

05:07.557 --> 05:09.017
(knocking)

05:12.229 --> 05:14.856
‐Dad!
‐There's my Maximus.

05:14.856 --> 05:15.857
(laughs)

05:16.316 --> 05:17.234
Douglas.

05:17.651 --> 05:19.069
Judith.

05:20.278 --> 05:21.822
Okay. If you need me,

05:21.822 --> 05:24.157
I left the number where
I'm at on the fridge.

05:24.157 --> 05:26.910
But only call me if
it's absolutely necessary.

05:26.910 --> 05:28.203
Why?

05:28.203 --> 05:31.206
Both:
Because it's your
girls' weekend.

05:31.540 --> 05:34.000
No. It's my...

05:34.000 --> 05:36.753
Both:
"Do Not Disturb" girls' weekend.

05:37.504 --> 05:39.714
That's right.
So from this point forward,

05:39.714 --> 05:41.842
do not disturb me.

05:41.842 --> 05:44.427
‐(phone ringing)
‐Okay, after this phone call,

05:44.427 --> 05:46.179
‐do not disturb me.
‐(ringing)

05:49.224 --> 05:51.685
You ready for the best
boys' weekend ever?

05:52.102 --> 05:54.187
Oh yeah! I was thinking

05:54.187 --> 05:56.606
we should eat hot dogs
for every meal.

05:56.606 --> 05:58.441
Done.

05:58.441 --> 06:01.069
And we should
try to get tickets
for the Daredevil Games.

06:01.069 --> 06:02.529
Oh.

06:02.529 --> 06:04.865
That ticket is
impossible to get.

06:04.865 --> 06:06.074
No one could pull that off.

06:06.825 --> 06:07.826
You're right.

06:08.493 --> 06:10.120
Except me. (laughs)

06:10.662 --> 06:11.997
Dad, you're the best!

06:14.207 --> 06:15.417
You're not gonna
believe it.

06:15.417 --> 06:17.711
My girlfriend got the flu!

06:17.711 --> 06:19.588
My Do Not Disturb
weekend got disturbed

06:19.588 --> 06:21.506
before it even started!

06:22.215 --> 06:24.134
I'm sorry to hear that.

06:24.134 --> 06:25.844
But, don't worry about me.

06:25.844 --> 06:27.846
I'll just find a motel
for the weekend.

06:28.263 --> 06:30.515
Doug, you don't have
to stay at a motel.

06:30.515 --> 06:32.267
There are plenty
of hotels in town.

06:33.560 --> 06:34.603
Why can't he just stay here?

06:34.978 --> 06:37.397
‐What?
‐Doug, let me handle this.

06:38.440 --> 06:40.108
What?

06:41.067 --> 06:43.069
Why not? He used to live here.

06:43.069 --> 06:45.322
Honey, I don't think
that's the best idea.

06:45.322 --> 06:47.032
Yeah, son. Your mom's right.

06:48.074 --> 06:49.117
Come on, Mom.

06:49.117 --> 06:51.202
I never get to see him.

06:51.202 --> 06:52.829
Please?

06:55.248 --> 06:57.208
‐Fine.
‐Yes!

06:57.208 --> 06:59.002
Boys' weekend is back on!

06:59.002 --> 07:01.588
I really appreciate
this, Judy.

07:01.588 --> 07:02.839
And to thank you,
I've got

07:02.839 --> 07:04.591
a little ukulele
song I can play.

07:05.634 --> 07:07.844
Oh, you know where they
love ukulele music?

07:07.844 --> 07:09.471
That hotel across town.

07:10.430 --> 07:12.891
♪ ♪

07:13.767 --> 07:15.852
Hi! Are you
interested in joining

07:15.852 --> 07:17.562
the coolest club in school?

07:17.896 --> 07:20.065
Wait? Is this DJ Club?

07:21.524 --> 07:24.653
No. This is Emergency
Preparedness Club.

07:24.653 --> 07:26.946
I'm Olive, the president.

07:26.946 --> 07:28.823
We may not light up a party,

07:28.823 --> 07:31.534
but we can light up
your outdoor staircase.

07:34.079 --> 07:35.789
Do I get one of
those whistles?

07:35.789 --> 07:38.083
And this stylish vest.

07:38.083 --> 07:41.419
Trust me.
This club will prepare you
to handle everything.

07:41.419 --> 07:43.338
A tsunami, a tornado,

07:43.338 --> 07:45.048
unexpected playground injuries.

07:45.590 --> 07:46.883
What about a zombie attack?

07:46.883 --> 07:49.552
That's ridiculous, but yes.

07:51.096 --> 07:52.347
Then I'm in!

07:52.347 --> 07:54.307
Sounds like you're
prepared for everything.

07:56.601 --> 07:59.312
Well, I wouldn't
say everything.

07:59.312 --> 08:01.606
There are some disasters
you don't see coming.

08:01.940 --> 08:03.733
You know, like an earthquake.

08:03.733 --> 08:06.236
Sure, you can throw some
granola bars in a backpack,

08:06.236 --> 08:07.696
but are you really
prepared when it suddenly

08:07.696 --> 08:08.947
splits your house in two?

08:08.947 --> 08:10.365
Or when the very ground
you're standing on

08:10.365 --> 08:12.200
disappears under your feet?

08:12.200 --> 08:14.703
Or when everything you know
and love is swept away?!

08:15.286 --> 08:18.456
Yeah, definitely
gonna join DJ Club.

08:21.042 --> 08:22.335
Olive, are you okay?

08:23.086 --> 08:24.796
Yeah.

08:24.796 --> 08:27.674
I just finally realized
this club is useless.

08:27.674 --> 08:29.968
If I can't prepare
for everything,

08:29.968 --> 08:32.303
why should I prepare
for anything?

08:32.303 --> 08:33.054
I quit.

08:34.639 --> 08:36.433
But Olive,
you love this club.

08:36.433 --> 08:39.018
Are you sure this isn't
about the divorce?

08:39.018 --> 08:42.021
Nope. It's about wearing
this ridiculous vest.

08:43.148 --> 08:44.649
Hi, Olive. I'm here
for the next shift.

08:44.649 --> 08:46.192
Anything to report?

08:46.192 --> 08:48.987
Yeah. Congratulations, Derek.
You're president now.

08:49.779 --> 08:51.990
‐Seriously?
‐Olive!

08:54.451 --> 08:56.703
Corn dogs for lunch
and now this?

08:56.703 --> 08:58.872
Everything's coming up Derek!

08:58.872 --> 09:00.206
♪ ♪

09:02.375 --> 09:04.794
♪ ♪

09:07.338 --> 09:10.008
Oh, uh, did you wanna watch TV?
I'll get out of your hair.

09:10.008 --> 09:11.634
Actually, I wanna read my book.

09:11.634 --> 09:12.677
Hey, I read that!

09:13.553 --> 09:14.554
Have you got to
the part where...

09:16.056 --> 09:18.808
Doug shuts his trap
and leaves Judy alone?

09:23.354 --> 09:25.440
Huh.

09:25.440 --> 09:27.108
I can't believe you still
have this old thing.

09:27.108 --> 09:28.610
You remember the day
we bought it?

09:28.610 --> 09:31.529
We went to every single
lamp store in town
and found nothing.

09:31.529 --> 09:33.448
Until we walked
past the pet store.

09:34.574 --> 09:35.825
And there it was
in the window.

09:35.825 --> 09:37.911
Our lamp,

09:37.911 --> 09:40.413
‐warming a discounted iguana.
‐(laughs)

09:41.289 --> 09:43.249
I still can't believe
you charmed the owner

09:43.249 --> 09:45.794
into selling it to us
with a ukulele song.

09:45.794 --> 09:48.254
Hey, nobody can
resist a ukulele.

09:48.254 --> 09:49.672
See these pants?

09:49.672 --> 09:50.924
Got 'em half off.

09:53.176 --> 09:54.511
I guess we had
some fun times, huh?

09:55.929 --> 09:58.890
‐We did.
‐Till I messed things up.

10:00.683 --> 10:01.684
Sorry, Judy.

10:02.477 --> 10:03.478
Thanks, Doug.

10:03.853 --> 10:06.189
(lamp fizzling)

10:06.189 --> 10:08.024
You know, I still
remember the trick

10:08.024 --> 10:09.192
to make it stop flickering.

10:09.901 --> 10:11.444
Alright. Let's see
what you got, hotshot.

10:11.444 --> 10:12.445
(blows)

10:13.571 --> 10:14.614
(stops fizzling)

10:14.614 --> 10:16.533
(both laugh)

10:16.533 --> 10:18.034
Well done, sir!

10:18.034 --> 10:19.202
Thank you, m'lady.

10:23.123 --> 10:24.749
Hey, guys! What's going on?

10:24.749 --> 10:26.459
‐Maximus.
‐Hey,

10:26.459 --> 10:28.378
you wanna hear your
dad's lamp song?

10:28.378 --> 10:30.630
‐Really?
‐Go for it!

10:30.630 --> 10:31.631
Oh ho!

10:34.592 --> 10:35.426
(clears throat)

10:35.426 --> 10:37.220
♪ $100, no ♪

10:37.220 --> 10:38.930
♪ $1,000, no ♪

10:38.930 --> 10:42.142
♪ $1,000,000, no because
the lamp is not for sale ♪

10:42.142 --> 10:45.103
♪ I'd offer you my car,
I'd offer you my house ♪

10:45.103 --> 10:46.271
♪ But you'd just
yell "get out" ♪

10:46.271 --> 10:47.480
♪ Because the lamp
is not for sale ♪

10:47.981 --> 10:49.232
♪ Just name a number, please ♪

10:49.232 --> 10:51.359
♪ I'm begging on my knees ♪

10:51.359 --> 10:53.695
♪ It's dark and I can't
see because the lamp ♪

10:53.695 --> 10:56.447
♪ Is not for sale! ♪

10:56.447 --> 10:57.448
(strumming)

10:57.991 --> 11:00.076
‐(clapping)
‐(laughing)

11:00.076 --> 11:02.662
Again, well done, sir!

11:02.662 --> 11:04.414
Again, thank you, m'lady.

11:05.498 --> 11:07.792
You know, I just remembered
I need something in the kitchen.

11:11.379 --> 11:14.632
(dialing)

11:15.341 --> 11:18.136
(ringing)

11:19.345 --> 11:22.473
‐Hello?
‐Alisha! You're not
gonna believe this.

11:22.473 --> 11:25.185
‐It's a miracle!
‐You finished all your homework?

11:26.853 --> 11:28.855
No! It's my parents.

11:28.855 --> 11:30.773
They're getting
along so well.

11:30.773 --> 11:34.235
They're laughing and singing
and sitting on the same couch.

11:34.235 --> 11:36.321
I think they could
get back together!

11:36.321 --> 11:38.615
Really? Are you sure?

11:38.615 --> 11:41.326
Yeah. They just need a little
push in the right direction.

11:43.036 --> 11:45.830
I know. I should make
them a romantic dinner!

11:45.830 --> 11:47.290
(laughs) Man,

11:47.290 --> 11:49.667
I'm glad I saved this
Burger Hole coupon.

11:51.544 --> 11:54.923
Little tip. Nothing romantic
comes in a greasy bag.

11:56.799 --> 11:58.509
Why don't I come over
and help you cook?

11:59.052 --> 12:01.804
Really?
You'd do that? Thanks.

12:02.222 --> 12:05.058
Wow. Not only am I gonna get
my parents back together,

12:06.059 --> 12:08.186
I also get to keep
my Burger Hole coupon.

12:10.271 --> 12:12.315
Well, we better get
cracking on our homework

12:12.315 --> 12:15.443
‐because I've got
a ton of math.
‐Really?

12:15.443 --> 12:17.987
We're not gonna talk about
what happened at school today?

12:17.987 --> 12:19.739
That you quit
Emergency Preparedness?

12:19.739 --> 12:21.366
What's to talk about?

12:22.325 --> 12:24.535
Problem one.
A train leaves Chicago

12:24.535 --> 12:26.120
at 1:00 PM,
heading for New York‐‐

12:26.120 --> 12:27.830
But, EPC is your thing.

12:28.248 --> 12:29.958
I mean, your yearbook
picture was you wrapping

12:29.958 --> 12:31.626
a drinking fountain
in caution tape.

12:33.086 --> 12:34.671
Anyway, back to the train‐‐

12:34.671 --> 12:36.881
Olive, stop changing
the subject.

12:37.340 --> 12:39.592
You're obviously upset
about your parents.

12:39.592 --> 12:41.886
Please. Talk to me.

12:42.887 --> 12:44.973
Syd, I love that
you're so concerned,

12:44.973 --> 12:47.100
but all I wanna do is

12:47.100 --> 12:49.852
forget about the divorce
and just hang with my bestie.

12:50.603 --> 12:53.106
Can you just let me do that?
Please?

12:54.065 --> 12:56.526
Yes. Of course I can.

12:56.526 --> 12:58.194
Good, now let me concentrate,

12:58.194 --> 13:00.071
or this train's never
gonna leave Chicago.

13:01.155 --> 13:04.284
♪ ♪

13:04.701 --> 13:06.452
Alright, I think
you're all set.

13:06.452 --> 13:08.830
Just remember,
serve the appetizer first.

13:10.206 --> 13:11.791
Uh...

13:11.791 --> 13:13.001
It's the little plate, Max.

13:14.711 --> 13:16.796
Now I've gotta get home.
Good luck!

13:16.796 --> 13:17.839
Thanks for everything,
Alisha.

13:27.015 --> 13:28.099
Dinner's ready!

13:30.977 --> 13:33.146
What's all this?

13:33.146 --> 13:35.732
I just wanted to make
you two a special dinner.

13:35.732 --> 13:37.317
To say thank you for,

13:37.317 --> 13:38.693
uh...

13:38.693 --> 13:39.986
for, uh...

13:39.986 --> 13:41.529
Being such great parents?

13:41.529 --> 13:42.739
Sure. That'll do.

13:44.449 --> 13:46.951
So please,
sit and enjoy.

13:46.951 --> 13:49.746
Courtesy of
Bistro Maxwell.

13:51.456 --> 13:52.832
Well, isn't this nice?

13:52.832 --> 13:55.043
Yeah. A little too nice.

14:00.590 --> 14:03.885
Tonight, we'll be starting with
some delicious artichoke...

14:03.885 --> 14:07.096
"hearts."
With a "kiss" of olive oil.

14:07.847 --> 14:10.683
I'll be back in a...
"couple" of minutes.

14:13.311 --> 14:14.729
Well, aren't you
gonna join us?

14:15.354 --> 14:18.316
I would, but I really need
to focus on the kitchen.

14:18.316 --> 14:20.068
You two just focus on the food.

14:20.568 --> 14:21.778
And each other.

14:24.989 --> 14:26.991
Okay, he's up to something.

14:28.117 --> 14:29.494
Do you think he's trying
to get us back together?

14:29.494 --> 14:30.953
Nah.

14:30.953 --> 14:33.206
(smooth jazz playing)

14:33.206 --> 14:35.583
Okay, he wants to
get us back together.

14:36.584 --> 14:38.669
‐Aw, Max.
‐What do we do now?

14:38.669 --> 14:40.713
We let him down gently.

14:42.465 --> 14:43.758
So, folks,

14:43.758 --> 14:45.426
how's everything
tasting this evening?

14:46.677 --> 14:47.929
Max...

14:49.013 --> 14:50.014
(shuts off music)

14:51.057 --> 14:53.684
We love everything that
you've done here tonight.

14:54.435 --> 14:57.230
But, honey, just because your
dad and I are getting along,

14:58.064 --> 15:00.066
doesn't mean we're
getting back together.

15:00.066 --> 15:01.859
It's true.

15:02.527 --> 15:03.778
I'm sorry, son.

15:05.363 --> 15:07.615
But I saw you.

15:07.615 --> 15:09.242
You were laughing
and having fun.

15:09.951 --> 15:11.327
Can't you just
be married again?

15:13.246 --> 15:15.498
‐Sweetheart...
‐I hate when you do that!

15:15.498 --> 15:17.500
You say "sweetheart"
instead of no

15:17.500 --> 15:19.460
because you think
it sounds nicer.

15:19.460 --> 15:22.171
But it's actually worse!
Just say what you mean.

15:24.423 --> 15:26.676
We're never gonna
be a family again.

15:27.301 --> 15:29.720
♪ ♪

15:34.767 --> 15:36.811
Pizza's here!
Get it while it's hot.

15:36.811 --> 15:37.937
Hey, Iggy.

15:37.937 --> 15:39.897
Notice anything different?

15:39.897 --> 15:41.899
Uh, the pizza's actually hot?

15:42.942 --> 15:46.362
No. Don't I look like a guy
who just got promotioned?

15:47.488 --> 15:49.198
Now you do!

15:50.116 --> 15:53.494
You're looking at the new
senior executive delivery dude.

15:53.494 --> 15:56.038
Yup. Iggy's got a bigger
piece of the pie.

15:56.038 --> 15:57.623
Oh, you got a raise, too?

15:57.623 --> 15:59.959
Nope. Just now
when I order pizza,

15:59.959 --> 16:02.086
they cut my slices bigger.

16:03.129 --> 16:04.797
Wait, isn't that
the same amount of...

16:06.257 --> 16:07.967
Congratulations, Iggy!

16:08.718 --> 16:10.928
Thanks. Don't worry.

16:10.928 --> 16:13.139
I'm still the same old Iggy.

16:13.139 --> 16:14.599
Because if I wasn't,

16:14.599 --> 16:15.975
who else would I be?

16:17.185 --> 16:18.561
Whoa...

16:25.276 --> 16:26.819
Oh hey, just in time.
Pizza's here,

16:26.819 --> 16:28.196
and I got it just
the way you like it.

16:28.196 --> 16:29.739
Spicy chicken meatballs
and green peppers.

16:29.739 --> 16:30.948
Yeah, whatever.

16:31.908 --> 16:33.534
What's wrong?

16:33.534 --> 16:36.162
I tried to talk to Olive
about the divorce, and...

16:36.162 --> 16:38.206
she refused.

16:38.206 --> 16:39.457
I'm really worried
about her, Dad.

16:39.457 --> 16:41.209
She quit Emergency
Preparedness Club.

16:41.209 --> 16:43.961
Syd, it's okay.
Olive's going through
a lot right now.

16:43.961 --> 16:45.463
She might do some things
that don't make sense,

16:45.463 --> 16:47.048
but that's just how
she's dealing with it.

16:47.048 --> 16:48.507
But it's just really
hard to sit back

16:48.507 --> 16:50.259
and watch her hold all this in.

16:50.259 --> 16:52.094
I know it is.

16:52.094 --> 16:54.055
Everything in her life
is up in the air right now.

16:54.055 --> 16:56.724
The one stable thing
she has is you.

16:56.724 --> 16:58.601
The best thing
you can do for Olive
is just be there for her.

16:59.352 --> 17:01.479
Okay, Dad. You're right.

17:02.188 --> 17:04.565
How about this?
Before Olive goes home,

17:04.565 --> 17:06.150
let's just have a nice
family pizza night together.

17:07.485 --> 17:10.363
Okay, I heard "Olive"
and I heard "pizza."

17:10.363 --> 17:13.324
As long as you're not talking
about olive pizza, I'm in.

17:17.620 --> 17:20.164
Hey, fam! Hey, O!
‐Hey, Grandma J!

17:20.164 --> 17:22.333
‐Grandma, welcome back!
‐Hey, Mom.

17:22.333 --> 17:24.335
How was your Do Not Disturb
Girls' Weekend?

17:24.335 --> 17:26.796
Undisturbed, thank you.

17:26.796 --> 17:28.798
Ooh! Pizza!
Don't mind if I do.

17:30.049 --> 17:32.677
So, tell us more about
your trip, Grandma!

17:32.677 --> 17:34.887
The spa was a‐ma‐zing!

17:35.680 --> 17:36.806
I spent most
of the weekend

17:36.806 --> 17:38.724
up to my neck in mud.

17:39.308 --> 17:41.394
I think you brought some
home behind your ear.

17:41.978 --> 17:44.272
I was trying for a robe, but
this is all I could sneak out.

17:44.272 --> 17:45.106
(giggles)

17:45.815 --> 17:48.818
Alright, so before I start
my slice, I need to know

17:48.818 --> 17:51.028
‐who's getting the crust?
‐Both: I call it!

17:51.028 --> 17:52.029
It's a tie!
You know what that means.

17:52.697 --> 17:54.365
Both:
Crust, paper, scissor, shoot!

17:54.365 --> 17:55.700
Scissors cuts crust.
I win!

17:57.868 --> 18:00.121
You know, as much fun
as I had this weekend,

18:00.121 --> 18:02.206
I really missed sitting
around with you goofballs.

18:02.206 --> 18:04.000
We missed you,
too, Grandma.

18:07.211 --> 18:08.337
Something wrong, Olive?

18:09.839 --> 18:11.007
Yes.

18:12.675 --> 18:14.552
I'm never gonna have this again.

18:15.720 --> 18:16.846
What do you mean?

18:17.346 --> 18:18.389
This.

18:18.973 --> 18:20.308
A family.

18:20.850 --> 18:22.602
Everything's falling apart.

18:23.436 --> 18:24.770
I mean,

18:24.770 --> 18:27.023
who am I gonna live with?

18:27.023 --> 18:29.233
Where am I gonna spend holidays?

18:29.233 --> 18:31.319
What happens if
I wanna curl my hair

18:31.319 --> 18:32.737
at my dad's place,

18:32.737 --> 18:34.822
but my curling iron's
at my mom's?

18:34.822 --> 18:36.407
How can I live my life
if I don't even know

18:36.407 --> 18:37.783
where to leave my curling iron?

18:37.783 --> 18:39.493
It's gonna be okay, Olive.

18:39.493 --> 18:41.454
We'll help you figure it out.

18:41.454 --> 18:43.247
That's easy for you to say.

18:43.247 --> 18:45.625
You have a great
family that's together.

18:47.376 --> 18:48.127
I don't.

18:51.213 --> 18:53.507
Which is why I'm never
going home again.

18:54.175 --> 18:55.217
Ever.

18:55.217 --> 18:57.970
♪ ♪

19:00.306 --> 19:01.849
♪ ♪

19:01.849 --> 19:03.559
(knocking)

19:03.559 --> 19:04.935
Go away!

19:05.811 --> 19:06.812
(sighs)

19:08.147 --> 19:10.399
Max, we're so sorry if we
gave you the wrong idea.

19:11.525 --> 19:13.277
Yeah, son. Sometimes,

19:13.277 --> 19:15.154
we forget how tough
this divorce is on you.

19:16.322 --> 19:17.615
It's fine.

19:17.615 --> 19:19.450
So, we're not a family anymore.

19:19.450 --> 19:20.201
I'll get over it.

19:21.035 --> 19:23.162
Max, no matter what happens,

19:24.163 --> 19:25.998
I'll always
be your dad.

19:25.998 --> 19:27.875
And I'll always
be your mom.

19:27.875 --> 19:29.543
Your dad and I
may not be together,

19:29.543 --> 19:31.420
but we're both
still your family.

19:31.420 --> 19:33.756
And we'll both
always love you.

19:34.465 --> 19:35.841
Well, obviously.

19:36.550 --> 19:38.177
I'm very lovable.

19:39.762 --> 19:42.556
‐Well, you know something great
did come out of this weekend.
‐Yeah.

19:43.015 --> 19:44.684
Your dad and I
realized that

19:44.684 --> 19:46.936
even though we aren't
married anymore,

19:46.936 --> 19:48.229
we can still be friends.

19:50.231 --> 19:52.233
Well, it was really nice

19:52.233 --> 19:53.943
to be around you guys
when you were laughing

19:53.943 --> 19:55.736
and having fun together.

19:56.153 --> 19:58.155
So, if that's what
you mean by friends,

19:59.156 --> 20:00.616
I'll take it.

20:00.616 --> 20:03.619
♪ ♪

20:09.417 --> 20:11.127
Olive, are you okay?

20:12.378 --> 20:14.130
Is there anything
we can do for you?

20:14.797 --> 20:16.507
No.

20:17.133 --> 20:18.926
I'm sorry I ruined dinner.

20:18.926 --> 20:21.095
Oh, Olive, you didn't
ruin anything.

20:22.430 --> 20:23.848
You know, Olive,
I was about your age

20:23.848 --> 20:24.890
when my parents
got divorced.

20:24.890 --> 20:26.559
‐Really?
‐Yeah.

20:26.976 --> 20:28.477
And I wanted my family to be

20:28.477 --> 20:30.521
what it used to be,
too, but it never was.

20:30.521 --> 20:32.231
It turned into
something different.

20:32.231 --> 20:33.691
My mom and I became
our own little family.

20:33.691 --> 20:35.860
A great little family.

20:36.360 --> 20:38.112
And when my mom
passed away,

20:38.112 --> 20:40.239
I also thought my family
would never be the same.

20:41.157 --> 20:42.783
And it wasn't,

20:42.783 --> 20:45.119
but we moved in with
the world's coolest grandma.

20:45.494 --> 20:47.121
Guilty.

20:48.414 --> 20:51.459
And the three
of us became
our own great family.

20:51.459 --> 20:53.627
That's true. You did.

20:53.627 --> 20:55.546
And besides,
no matter what happens,

20:56.005 --> 20:57.923
your friends will help
you through this.

20:57.923 --> 20:59.425
You've got the bestest
bestie right next to you.

21:00.009 --> 21:01.761
Guilty.

21:03.387 --> 21:05.347
And I learned, Olive, that
your mom and dad love you

21:05.347 --> 21:06.640
and will always
be there for you,

21:06.640 --> 21:07.516
even if they're not together.

21:08.976 --> 21:10.561
Wow.

21:10.561 --> 21:11.937
This is a lot to take in.

21:11.937 --> 21:14.440
Yeah. You probably
need some space.

21:15.357 --> 21:16.734
That means you,
too, old dude.

21:21.238 --> 21:24.283
Do you want me to give
you some space, too?

21:25.201 --> 21:26.327
No.

21:26.327 --> 21:28.037
I want zero space from you.

21:28.537 --> 21:31.290
♪ ♪

21:33.501 --> 21:35.753
It's been almost an hour.
How do you think
the girls are doing?

21:35.753 --> 21:37.838
I don't know. Unlike you,

21:37.838 --> 21:39.965
I don't pretend I'm dusting
with my ear to the door.

21:42.510 --> 21:44.845
Oh hey, look who's here.
If you girls are still hungry,

21:44.845 --> 21:46.263
we've got a half
a pizza in the fridge,

21:46.263 --> 21:48.182
unless you wanna eat
it cold for breakfast.

21:48.182 --> 21:49.934
Actually,

21:49.934 --> 21:52.436
I won't be here for breakfast.

21:52.436 --> 21:53.521
I'm ready to go home.

21:54.313 --> 21:57.191
‐Really? I'm proud
of you, Olive.
‐So am I.

21:57.191 --> 21:59.819
Thanks. You guys are right.

21:59.819 --> 22:02.321
My family may be changing,

22:02.321 --> 22:04.406
but we'll still be a family.
Just different.

22:05.741 --> 22:07.076
So you wanna
call your mom now?

22:07.076 --> 22:09.036
Yeah. And while I wait,

22:09.036 --> 22:10.746
how about we
finish that pizza?

22:10.746 --> 22:11.747
I call crust!

22:12.623 --> 22:14.667
Fine, if you must.

22:14.667 --> 22:17.044
What's this? No fuss?

22:17.044 --> 22:18.796
Ooh! More rhymes!

22:18.796 --> 22:20.923
I didn't wreck it, I trust?

22:20.923 --> 22:22.675
Well now, it's a bust.

22:23.676 --> 22:25.302
JK. Eat my dust!

22:25.302 --> 22:28.055
♪ ♪

22:29.849 --> 22:31.350
This chicken piccata is amazing.

22:31.350 --> 22:32.601
Yeah, Max. It's delicious.

22:32.601 --> 22:34.019
So who cooked it?

22:35.271 --> 22:38.274
First of all, way to
not believe in me, Mom!

22:38.274 --> 22:39.817
And second, it was Alisha.

22:41.026 --> 22:42.403
Who's this Alisha?

22:42.903 --> 22:45.072
Just some girl. No big deal.

22:45.072 --> 22:46.365
Got it.
You have a crush on her.

22:48.742 --> 22:50.911
Dad! I never said that!

22:50.911 --> 22:52.121
Yeah, Doug.
He never said that.

22:52.121 --> 22:54.206
And by the way,
it's a giant crush.

22:56.333 --> 22:58.878
‐Guys, can we not
talk about this?
‐Sorry.

23:00.212 --> 23:03.007
You know, I can teach you
to play the ukulele.

23:03.007 --> 23:04.049
It's how I won over your mom.

23:04.049 --> 23:07.177
You won me over
in spite of the ukulele.

23:08.929 --> 23:10.598
So when do I get
to meet this Alisha?

23:10.598 --> 23:12.975
Or do I have to wait
until you two are
walking down the aisle?

23:12.975 --> 23:14.685
(both giggle)

23:15.144 --> 23:16.812
Okay, you've had your fun.

23:16.812 --> 23:18.480
Can we just stop
talking about this now?

23:18.480 --> 23:19.940
‐Okay, sorry.
‐Doug: Sorry.

23:19.940 --> 23:21.025
You're right.

23:22.109 --> 23:23.402
You really think
Alisha would like it

23:23.402 --> 23:25.070
‐if I learned to
play the ukulele?
‐Judy: Hey.

23:25.070 --> 23:27.781
If it got us a broken lamp,
it can do anything.

23:27.781 --> 23:30.117
♪ ♪

23:31.535 --> 23:34.121
<i>♪ Do do, do do do do, do do ♪</i>

23:36.290 --> 23:39.001
<i>♪ Do do, do do do do, do do ♪</i>

23:48.093 --> 23:50.971
<i>♪ Do do, do do do do, do do ♪</i>

23:52.890 --> 23:55.893
<i>♪ Do do, do do do do, do do ♪</i>

23:57.686 --> 23:59.063
Man:
<i>Oh yeah.</i>
